A'(x) D'(y) = - \alpha A(x) D'(y) - \beta A'(x) D(y)
 {A'(x) + \alpha A(x) \over A'(x) } = -\beta{ D(y) \over D'(y)}.
f(x, y) = A \exp(-i p x -i q y),\quad g(x, y) = B \exp(-i p x -i q y)
-i A p = \alpha (A - B), \quad -i B q = \beta (B - A)
